texts.text: >The battle with the demons continues...
*Pant* There's more of them than I thought there'd be...!
I knew it was gonna be hard, but this is getting ridiculous.
Goddammit, they're everywhere! This is so damn annoying!
Yo gatekeeper! Are we done yet?! Things are getting outta hand here!
Just a bit more. Hang in there!
You heard her guys! Time to dig deep!
If we dig any deeper we'll go out the other side!
Shit, watch out Ririn!
Aaargh!
>Megakin takes down the demon that was about to ambush Ririn just in time!
Sorry about that Megakin. Thanks for the save!

!!
Megakin, behind you!
>Demons are charging at Megakin while he is off balance!
Shit...!
No you don't.
I got you covered.
>You immediately cut in to cover Megakin's back.
Newbie...
...Holy shit! That was such a cool move!
Tell you what, you cover my back
and I'll cover yours. Aight?
Get yourselves together guys, we're almost there!
Yes, it's done! We pulled through!
Though this was just a quick patch, it should solve our problems for now.
I'm EXHAUSTED!!
We all got through it in one piece.
I think I lost a couple of pounds...
For you, that's just a margin.
...Oh, and by the way [sys user_name].
Thanks for saving my ass back there, I owe you one man.
Who'd have thought the day would come when you'd be the one saving my ass.
So much more dependable than when you first started off.
Maybe it's time to stop calling you Newbie, eh?
Yeah.
You're the one who needs help now Megakin, so maybe it's time to pass the torch to Newbie?
Newbie's such a vital part of the Liberators now, I wouldn't mind having Newbie as the leader.
So what's the new call sign for Newbie? Leader?
Hey, you guys never even call ME that!
*Laugh*
Hey! I don't care about regrets or tasty souls
or any of that!
Give me back [sys user_name]!
It's too late.
Once a human is enveloped by the fog, there's only one possible outcome.
There's no coming back.
No human's ever come back from the fog. Not a single one.
And even if we did know how to save your human, why would we want to do that?
We love to eat human souls!
Damn you!
>Pixie jumps on one of the demons and claws her in the face!
Ouch! That hurts!
What do you think you're doing you puny insect?!
If you're going to behave like that, then the gloves are off!
Everybody, get her!
*Moan*
Look at you shorty, you're all banged up. You're barely even alive.
Serves you right.
Don't you know how to count?
We're a posse, and you're all alone. You can't win against us!
...I am NOT alone...
Huh? What's that?
I'll tell you what. If you beg we can let you live.
How about it? You don't wanna die, do you? All you have to do is say "please".
No, I'm not gonna beg!
Give me back [sys user_name]!
Oh, you're not going to beg?
Die then!

Egh...
[sys user_name]!!!!!!
>Having stopped the demon outbreak, the Liberators return to the Hideout.
>You are taking up the rear, watching the rest of the gang.
>Relieved that the incident is over, they're all joking around and having fun.
>It's a sight full of warmth and tenderness, dazzling to behold.
>A sight that you deliberately cast away of your own accord...
...What's up yo? You growin' senile on me again?
If you don't catch up, we just might leave you behind.
...Newbie?
>Your friends all look at you in puzzlement.
>To them, you only say one thing.
...This is a dream.
I can't go on like this.
Here we go again, another one of Newbie's weird outbursts...
This is a dream, huh? What do you mean?
Yeah, I guess we've been through some pretty fantastical stuff since becoming Dx2s,
but why deny that it's real now?
You can't do what....?
Yo, you okay man? You've been actin' weird lately.
Aight man, I get it. We all deserve some R & R, so I'm gonna go all out with the celebration this time...
...[sys user_name]?
>You tell the Liberators your story.
>How you betrayed them and went to the side of the Acolytes.
>How you did it to save the world but ended up failing just the same.
>How the human race ended up destroying the world with ICBMs
>in an attempt to destroy each other.
I... Don't know what to say... I am at a lost for words...
Yeah, that story's just so out there that...
It's kind of hard to believe...
A hale of ICBMs ending the world?
If that was meant to be a joke, it's in bad taste.
Have you been affected by the evil spirits we were fighting? Is that why you're imagining all this?
And you betraying us to join the Acolytes...
That's impossible.
Hey, maybe that was the dream. The ICBMs I mean.
Okay...
Let's say there are two worlds. The one your were talking about and the one we're in right now.
And if one of them is a dream, which one would you rather it be?
If you could decide which one is real and which one is just a dream,
which will you choose?
You're here right now, livin' and breathin'.
And we're here too, livin' and breathin'.
Right?
>Megakin holds out his hand to you...
>The other members of the Liberators look on intently...
The butterfly's dream, the brain in a vat...
We've all doubted our own reality some time or other.
That we might be living in a dream.
But in the end, reality is what you make it to be.
You should know that.
You choose your own reality.
If you want, we can always fight side by side.
Yes. We're all here with you.
We always overcame the difficulties we faced together.
If there's something you can't handle alone, tell us!
Yeah! We'll be able to help you... Maybe?
But even if we can't, we can at least take some of the load off your back.
That's right. We're all willing to put in the effort when it comes to you.

Newbie... We're companions...
We're the Liberators... remember?
Don't hold everything in.
You don't have to go it alone.
Take my hand.
It's okay. Stop trying enduring all the pain and turmoil on your own.
>Somehow you know that if you take Megakin's hand, there's no turning back.
>But still...
>It may be a dream, it may be an illusion. But if you reach out your hand,
>if you want it hard enough, it can be reality.
>If so...
